Two men are fighting for their lives in hospital after scaffolding attached to a west London town hall collapsed this afternoon. Dozens of ambulances, fire engines and police cars descended on the scene in Hammersmith after the incident at 5.30pm. Two men who suffered potentially life threatening injuries were then rushed to a major trauma centre by air ambulance ‘as a priority’. A Metropolitan Police spokesperson said the force has now launched an investigation. The Health and Safety Executive, the government agency responsible for workplace welfare, has also been informed. Hammersmith and Fulham council said the incident was at a construction site run by Ardmore Construction Ltd. They were working on Hammersmith Town Hall’s new Civic Campus on Kings Street. The new site is set to include new homes, a cinema and a council building, MyLondon reports. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.